############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML Calculate the value of [`30-((2+3)\cdot2)\text{,}`] respecting the order that the grouping symbols are telling you to execute the arithmetic operations.
[_]{20}{10}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION The grouping symbols tell us what to work on first. In this exercise, we have grouping symbols within grouping symbols, so any operation in there (the addition) should be executed first:
[```\newcommand{\highlight}[1]{\mathchoice{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\displaystyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\textstyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\scriptstyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\scriptscriptstyle #1$}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} 30-\left((2+3)\cdot2\right)\amp=30-\left(\highlight{5}\cdot2\right)\\ \amp=30-\highlight{10}\\ \amp=\highlight{20} \end{aligned} ```]
END_PGML_SOLUTION
